# Release Workflow

## Release System Overview
This project uses semantic-release with separate configurations for each package.

## Release Configuration Files
- [.releaserc.json](mdc:.releaserc.json) - Root release configuration
- [packages/ui/.releaserc.json](mdc:packages/ui/.releaserc.json) - UI package release config
- [packages/common/.releaserc.json](mdc:packages/common/.releaserc.json) - Common package release config
- [packages/auth/.releaserc.json](mdc:packages/auth/.releaserc.json) - Auth package release config

## GitHub Actions Workflows
- [.github/workflows/selective-release.yml](mdc:.github/workflows/selective-release.yml) - Smart release (only changed packages)

## Release Process
1. **Automatic**: Push to main branch triggers selective release (only changed packages)
2. **Individual**: Use `pnpm release:ui`, `pnpm release:common`, or `pnpm release:auth`

## Commit Convention
Use conventional commits to trigger releases (see [commit-conventions.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/commit-conventions.mdc) for detailed guidelines):
- `feat(ui): add new component` - UI package minor release
- `fix(common): resolve utility bug` - Common package patch release
- `feat(auth): add login functionality` - Auth package minor release

## Package Versions
Each package maintains independent versioning:
- UI: Currently at version 1.3.4
- Common: Currently at version 0.1.0
- Auth: Currently at version 0.1.0

## Release Tags
- UI: `@trash-kit/ui-v${version}`
- Common: `@trash-kit/common-v${version}`
- Auth: `@trash-kit/auth-v${version}`

## Prerequisites
- NPM_TOKEN secret must be configured in GitHub repository
- Proper repository permissions for releases